A simple crossplatform 2D multiplayer shooter.

More infromation is available in the Wiki.

A demo can be found in the Releases section.

How to build under Ubuntu Linux:
  1. Install SFML-2.1
     http://www.sfml-dev.org/download/sfml/2.1/
     See the instructions below

  2. Install pugixml-1.2
     sudo apt-get install libpugixml-dev

  3. Install libconfig
     $ sudo apt-get install libconfig-dev

  4. Install ENetPlus.
     https://github.com/xairy/enet-plus

  5. Generate project files
     $ ./premake4 gmake

  6. $ cd build

  7. On x32 system:
     $ make config=release32
     On x64 system:
     $ make config=release64

How to install SFML-2.1:
  1. Install cmake
     $ sudo apt-get install cmake
  2. Install the required dependencies
     $ sudo apt-get install libpthread-stubs0-dev libgl1-mesa-dev \
       libxrandr-dev libfreetype6-dev libglew-dev libjpeg8-dev \
       libsndfile1-dev libopenal-dev
  3. Download and extract SFML-2.1-sources.zip
     http://www.sfml-dev.org/download/sfml/2.1/
  4. $ cd SFML-2.1
  5. $ cmake .
  6. $ make
  7. $ sudo make install

How to start server:
  1. Set port in blowmorph/data/server.cfg
  2. $ ./server.sh

How to start client:
  1. Set server's port and ip in blowmorph/data/client.cfg
  2. $ ./client.sh

How to build under Microsoft Windows, Visual Studio 2008:
  1. Install Python 2.7.6
  2. Run "premake4.exe vs2008"
  3. Build build\blowmorph.sln
